==English==
===Etymology===
From Modern English huckle and buck, def. 1 first used by David A. Fleisher.

===Noun===
'''hucklebuck''' (''plural:'' '''hucklebucks''')

#A redneck, hillbilly, or otherwise culturally backwards person, usually descended from the [[Amish]] or [[Pennsylvania Dutch]] and residing in central Pennsylvania.

#A sexual position.